Mexico Reports 172.5 Billion Peso Budget Deficit Through August

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   R o e d e r
-- 
2011-09-30T19:35:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/mexico-reports-172-5-billion-peso-budget-deficit-through-august.html
Mexico  reported a budget deficit of
172.5 billion pesos in the first eight months of the year, the
 Finance Ministry  said today in an e-mailed statement.  Mexico had a budget deficit of 164 billion pesos in the
first seven months, according to a statement published Aug. 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Roeder in Mexico City at 
 jroeder@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
